Search within the title, abstract, claims, or full patent document: You can restrict your search to a specific field using field names.

Use TI= to search in the title, AB= for the abstract, CL= for the claims, or TAC= for all three. For example, TI=(safety belt).

Search by Cooperative Patent Classifications (CPCs): These are commonly used to represent ideas in place of keywords, and can also be entered in a search term box. If you're searching forseat belts, you could also search for B60R22/00 to retrieve documents that mention safety belts or body harnesses. CPC=B60R22 will match documents with exactly this CPC, CPC=B60R22/low matches documents with this CPC or a child classification of this CPC.

Keywords and boolean syntax (USPTO or EPO format): seat belt searches these two words, or their plurals and close synonyms. "seat belt" searches this exact phrase, in order. -seat -belt searches for documents not containing either word.

For searches using boolean logic, the default operator is AND with left associativity. Note: this means safety OR seat belt is searched as (safety OR seat) AND belt. Each word automatically includes plurals and close synonyms. Adjacent words that are implicitly ANDed together, such as (safety belt), are treated as a phrase when generating synonyms.

Description
translated from Portuguese

1/1101/110

Relatrio Descritivo da Patente de Inveno para: COMPOSIO QUE COMPREENDE UM AGENTE DE CONTROLE BIOLGICO E UM FUNGICIDA, SEUS USOS, SEMENTE RESISTENTE A PATGENO, MTODO PARA REDUZIR OS DANOS TOTAIS EM PLANTAS E EM PARTES DE PLANTAS, E KIT DE PARTES.Invention Patent Descriptive Report for: COMPOSITION THAT UNDERSTANDS A BIOLOGICAL CONTROL AGENT AND A FUNGICIDE, ITS USES, PATHOGEN RESISTANT SEED, METHOD TO REDUCE TOTAL DAMAGES IN PLANTS AND IN PLANTS PARTS, AND PARTS KIT.

[001] A presente inveno diz respeito a uma composio que compreende pelo menos um agente de controle biolgico selecionado entre microrganismos especficos e/ou um mutante de tais cepas que possua todas as caractersticas identificativas da cepa respectiva e/ou um metabolito produzido pela cepa respectiva que exiba atividade contra insetos, caros, nematodes e/ou fitopatognicos, e pelo menos um fungicida (I) selecionado do grupo consistindo nos inibidores da biossntese de ergosterol, numa quantidade sinergicamente eficaz. Alm disso, a presente inveno diz respeito utilizao de tal composio, bem como a um mtodo para reduzir os dados totais em plantas e em partes de plantas.[001] The present invention relates to a composition that comprises at least one biological control agent selected from specific microorganisms and / or a mutant of such strains that has all the identifying characteristics of the respective strain and / or a metabolite produced by the respective strain that exhibits activity against insects, mites, nematodes and / or phytopathogens, and at least one fungicide (I) selected from the group consisting of ergosterol biosynthesis inhibitors, in a synergistically effective amount. In addition, the present invention concerns the use of such a composition, as well as a method for reducing the total data on plants and parts of plants.

[002] Os inseticidas ou fungicidas sintticos so frequentemente no especficos e, assim, podem atuar sobre microrganismos diferentes dos microrganismos alvo, incluindo outros organismos benficos que ocorram naturalmente. Devido sua natureza qumica, estes tambm podem ser txicos e no biodegradveis. Os consumidores de todo o mundo esto cada vez mais conscientes dos problemas ambientais e em termos de sade potenciais associados aos resduos de qumicos, em particular em produtos alimentares. Tal resultou numa presso crescente por parte dos consumidores para reduzir a utilizao ou pelo menos a quantidade de pesticidas qumicos (isto , sintticos). Assim, existe uma necessidade para gerir os requisitos da cadeia alimentar, garantindo ainda um controle eficaz de pragas.[002] Synthetic insecticides or fungicides are often non-specific and thus can act on microorganisms other than the target microorganisms, including other beneficial organisms that occur naturally. Due to their chemical nature, they can also be toxic and non-biodegradable. Consumers around the world are increasingly aware of the potential environmental and health problems associated with chemical residues, particularly in food products. This has resulted in increasing pressure from consumers to reduce the use or at least the amount of chemical (ie synthetic) pesticides. Thus, there is a need to manage the requirements of the food chain, while still ensuring effective pest control.

Petio 870190055580, de 17/06/2019, pg. 7/130Petition 870190055580, of 06/17/2019, p. 7/130

2/110 [003] Um outro problema que surge atravs da utilizao de inseticidas ou fungicidas sintticos consiste no fato da aplicao repetida e exclusiva de um inseticida ou fungicida provoca, frequentemente, uma seleo de microrganismos resistentes. Normalmente, tais cepas tambm so inter-resistentes contra outros ingredientes ativos que apresentem o mesmo modo de ao. Um controle eficaz dos patgenos com os referidos compostos ativos deixa ento de ser possvel. No entanto, os ingredientes ativos com novos mecanismos de ao so difceis e o seu desenvolvimento caro.2/110 [003] Another problem that arises through the use of synthetic insecticides or fungicides is the fact that repeated and exclusive application of an insecticide or fungicide often causes a selection of resistant microorganisms. Usually, such strains are also inter-resistant against other active ingredients that have the same mode of action. Effective control of pathogens with said active compounds is then no longer possible. However, the active ingredients with new mechanisms of action are difficult and their development is expensive.

[004] O risco do desenvolvimento de resistncia em populaes de patgenos, bem como as preocupaes em termos ambientais e de sade para os seres humanos, promoveu o interesse na identificao de alternativas aos inseticidas e fungicidas sintticos para o controle de doenas de plantas. A utilizao de agentes de controle biolgico (BCA) constitui uma alternativa. No entanto, a eficcia da maioria dos BCA no est ao mesmo nvel dos inseticidas e fungicidas convencionais, em particular no caso da presso de uma infeco grave. Assim sendo, os agentes de controle biolgico conhecidos, os seus mutantes e os metabolitos produzidos por estes so, em particular, em taxas de aplicao reduzidas, no totalmente satisfatrios.[004] The risk of developing resistance in populations of pathogens, as well as environmental and health concerns for humans, has promoted interest in identifying alternatives to synthetic insecticides and fungicides for the control of plant diseases. The use of biological control agents (BCA) is an alternative. However, the effectiveness of most BCAs is not at the same level as conventional insecticides and fungicides, particularly in the case of pressure from a serious infection. Therefore, the known biological control agents, their mutants and the metabolites produced by them are, in particular, at reduced rates of application, which are not entirely satisfactory.

[005] Assim, existe uma necessidade constante para o desenvolvimento de novos agentes para a proteo de plantas alternativos que, em algumas reas, pelo menos ajudem a satisfazer os requisitos supramencionados.[005] Thus, there is a constant need for the development of new agents for the protection of alternative plants that, in some areas, at least help to satisfy the requirements mentioned above.

[006] O exemplo 13 do documento descreve um efeito sinrgico de uma mistura que compreende Bacillus subtilis AQ713 (N de[006] Example 13 of the document describes a synergistic effect of a mixture comprising Bacillus subtilis AQ713 (No.

Acesso NRRL: B-21661) e azoxistrobina. No entanto, devido natureza do sinergismo, no possvel prever o efeito de outrosNRRL access: B-21661) and azoxystrobin. However, due to the nature of synergism, it is not possible to predict the effect of other

Petio 870190055580, de 17/06/2019, pg. 8/130Petition 870190055580, of 06/17/2019, p. 8/130

3/110 agentes de controle biolgico em combinaes com outro fungicida com base neste exemplo especfico.3/110 biological control agents in combinations with another fungicide based on this specific example.

[007] luz do referidos antes, constitui, em particular, um objeto da presente inveno proporcionar composies que exibam atividade contra insetos, caros, nematodes e/ou fitopatognicos. Alm do mais, constitui ainda um objeto particular da presente inveno reduzir as taxas de aplicao e alargar o espectro de atividade dos agentes de controle biolgico e dos fungicidas, proporcionando assim uma composio que, de preferncia numa quantidade total reduzida de compostos ativos aplicados, apresente uma atividade melhorada contra insetos, caros, nematodes e/ou fitopatognicos. Em particular, constitui um outro objeto da presente inveno proporcionar uma composio que, quando aplicada a uma cultura, proporcione uma quantidade diminuda de resduos na cultura, reduzindo assim o risco de desenvolvimento de resistncia, proporcionando, apesar disso, um controle de doena eficaz.[007] In light of the above, it is, in particular, an object of the present invention to provide compositions that exhibit activity against insects, mites, nematodes and / or phytopathogens. Furthermore, it is also a particular object of the present invention to reduce application rates and to broaden the activity spectrum of biological control agents and fungicides, thus providing a composition that, preferably in a reduced total amount of active compounds applied, presents an improved activity against insects, mites, nematodes and / or phytopathogens. In particular, it is another object of the present invention to provide a composition that, when applied to a culture, provides a decreased amount of residues in the culture, thus reducing the risk of developing resistance, while providing effective disease control.

[008] Assim sendo, concluiu-se que estes objetos so, pelo menos parcialmente, solucionados pelas composies de acordo com a inveno, tais como a seguir definidas. De preferncia, a composio de acordo com a presente inveno satisfaz os requisitos supra descritos. De um modo surpreendente, concluiu-se que a aplicao da composio de acordo com a presente inveno, de um modo simultneo ou sequencial, a plantas, partes de plantas, frutos colhidos, locais de crescimento de vegetais e/ou plantas, permite, de preferncia, um melhor controle de insetos, caros, nematodes e/ou fitopatognicos, do que aquele que possvel, por um lado, com as cepas, com os seus mutantes e/ou com os seus metabolitos produzidos pelas cepas e, por outro lado, com os fungicidas individuais, por si ss (misturas sinrgicas). Atravs da aplicao do agente de controle biolgico e do fungicida especificado de acordo[008] Therefore, it was concluded that these objects are, at least partially, solved by the compositions according to the invention, as defined below. Preferably, the composition according to the present invention meets the requirements described above. Agentes de controle biolgico [0013] De um modo geral, um pesticida designa a aptido de uma substncia para aumentar a mortalidade ou inibir a taxa de crescimento de pragas de plantas. o termo aqui utilizado para descrever a propriedade de uma substncia para exibir atividade contra insetos, caros, nematodes e/ou fitopatognicos. No sentido da presente inveno, o termo pragas inclui insetos, caros, nematodes e/ou fitopatognicos.Biological control agents [0013] In general, a "pesticide" designates the ability of a substance to increase mortality or inhibit the growth rate of plant pests. the term is used here to describe the property of a substance to exhibit activity against insects, mites, nematodes and / or phytopathogens. In the sense of the present invention, the term "pests" includes insects, mites, nematodes and / or phytopathogens.

[0014] Tal como aqui utilizada, a expresso controle biolgico definida como o controle de um patgeno e/ou inseto e/ou acardeo e/ou nematode por meio da utilizao de um segundo organismo. Coo mecanismos conhecidos de controle biolgico refere-se bactrias[0014] As used herein, the term "biological control" is defined as the control of a pathogen and / or insect and / or mite and / or nematode through the use of a second organism. As known mechanisms of biological control refers to bacteria

[0015] O termo inseticidas, bem como o termo inseticida, designa a aptido de uma substncia para aumentar a mortalidade ou para inibir a taxa de crescimento de insetos. Tal como aqui utilizado, o termo insetos compreende todos os organismos da classe de Insecta. A expresso insetos pr-adultos designa qualquer forma de um organismo antes do estado adulto, incluindo, por exemplo, ovos, larvas e ninfas.[0015] The term "insecticides", as well as the term "insecticide", designates the ability of a substance to increase mortality or to inhibit the rate of growth of insects. As used herein, the term "insects" includes all organisms in the class of "Insecta". The term "pre-adult" insects refers to any form of an organism before its adult state, including, for example, eggs, larvae and nymphs.

[0016] Os termos nematicidas e nematicida designam a aptido de uma substncia para aumentar a mortalidade ou para inibir a taxa de crescimento de nematodes. De um modo geral, o termo nematode compreende ovos, larvas, formas juvenis e maduras do referido organismo.[0016] The terms "nematicides" and "nematicides" designate the ability of a substance to increase mortality or to inhibit the growth rate of nematodes. In general, the term nematode includes eggs, larvae, juvenile and mature forms of the organism.

[0017] Os termos acaricidas e acaricida designa a aptido de uma substncia para aumentar a mortalidade ou para inibir a taxa de crescimento de ectoparasitas que pertencem classe de Arachnida, sub-classe Acari.[0017] The terms "acaricides" and "acaricide" refer to the ability of a substance to increase mortality or to inhibit the growth rate of ectoparasites that belong to the Arachnida class, sub-class Acari.

[0018] O termo metabolito diz respeito a qualquer composto, substncia ou produto secundrio de uma fermentao de um microrganismo que possua atividade pesticida.[0018] The term "metabolite" refers to any compound, substance or secondary product of a fermentation of a microorganism that has pesticidal activity.

[0020] O termo variante designa uma cepa que possui todas as caractersticas identificativas dos nmeros de adeso NRRL ou ATCC tal como indicados no presente texto e pode ser identificada como tendo um genoma que hibrida sob condies de estringncia elevada no genoma dos nmeros de adeso NRRL ou ATCC.[0020] The term "variant" designates a strain that has all the identifying characteristics of the NRRL or ATCC membership numbers as indicated in this text and can be identified as having a genome that hybridizes under conditions of high stringency in the genome of the numbers of NRRL or ATCC membership.

[0021] O termo hibridao diz respeito a uma reao pela qual um ou mais polinucleotdeos reagem para formar um complexo que estabilizado atravs de pontes de hidrognio entre as bases dos resduos nucleotdeos. A formao de pontes de hidrognio pode ocorrer por emparelhamento de bases de Watson-Crick, ligao de Hoogstein ou de um outro modo qualquer especfico para sequncias. O complexo pode compreender duas cadeias que formam uma estrutura dplice, trs ou mais cadeias que formam um complexo com mltiplas cadeias, uma cadeia individual auto-hibridvel ou qualquer combinao destas. As reaes de hibridao podem ser efetuadas sob condies de diferente estringncia. De um modo geral, uma reao de hibridao de estringncia reduzida efetuada a cerca de 40C em 10 X SSC ou numa soluo de equivalente fora inica/temperatura. Uma hibridao de estringncia moderada tipicamente efetuada a cerca de 50C em 6 X SSC e uma reao de hibridao de estringncia elevada normalmente efetuada a cerca de 60C em 1 X SSC.[0021] The term "hybridization" refers to a reaction by which one or more polynucleotides react to form a complex that is stabilized by hydrogen bonds between the bases of the nucleotide residues. The formation of hydrogen bonds can occur by pairing Watson-Crick bases, Hoogstein bonding or some other specific sequence. The complex can comprise two chains that form a double structure, three or more chains that form a complex with multiple chains, an individual self-hybridizing chain or any combination thereof. Hybridization reactions can be carried out under conditions of different stringency. In general, a reduced stringency hybridization reaction is carried out at about 40 C in 10 X SSC or in a solution of equivalent ionic strength / temperature. A moderate stringency hybridization is typically carried out at about 50 C in 6 X SSC and a high stringency hybridization reaction is normally carried out at about 60 C in 1 X SSC.

Este alinhamento e a percentagem de homologia ou de identidade de sequncia pode ser determinada utilizando aplicaes informticas conhecidas na especialidade, por exemplo, as descritas em Current Protocols in Molecular Biology (F. M. Ausubel et al., eds., 1987), Suplemento 30, Seco 7. 7. 18, Quadro 7.8/110 more preferably, greater than 95% in relation to the genome with the indicated NRRL or ATCC adhesion number. A polynucleotide or a region of a polynucleotide (or a polypeptide or a region of a polypeptide) has a certain percentage (for example, 80%, 85%, 90% or 95%) of "sequence identity" relative to another sequence it means that, when aligned, that percentage of bases (or amino acids) are identical when comparing the two sequences. This alignment and the percentage of homology or sequence identity can be determined using computer applications known in the art, for example, those described in Current Protocols in Molecular Biology (FM Ausubel et al., Eds., 1987), Supplement 30, Section 7. 7. 18, Table 7.

[00129] No presente contexto, como penetrantes adequados referese todas aquelas substncias que so tipicamente utilizadas para melhorar a penetrao de compostos ativos sob o ponto de vista agroqumico nas plantas. Neste contexto, os penetrantes so definidos como sendo capazes de penetrar a cutcula da planta, a partir da mistura de aplicao (geralmente aquosa) e/ou a partir do revestimento pulverizado, sendo assim capazes de aumentar a mobilidade dos compostos ativos na cutcula. Para determinar estas propriedades possvel utilizar o mtodo descrito na literatura (Baur et al., 1997, Pesticide Science 51, 131-152). Como exemplos refere-se alcoxilatos de lcool, tais como etoxilato de gordura de coco (10) ou etoxilato de isotridecilo (12), steres de cidos gordos, por exemplo, steres metlicos de leo de colza ou de leo de soja, alcoxilatos de aminas gordas, por exemplo, etoxilato de tallowamina (15), ou sais de amnio e/ou de fosfnio, tais como, por exemplo, sulfato de amnio ou hidrogeno-fosfato de diamnio.[00129] In the present context, as suitable penetrants are all those substances that are typically used to improve the penetration of active compounds from the agrochemical point of view in plants. In this context, penetrants are defined as being able to penetrate the cuticle of the plant, from the application mixture (usually aqueous) and / or from the sprayed coating, thus being able to increase the mobility of the active compounds in the cuticle. To determine these properties, it is possible to use the method described in the literature (Baur et al., 1997, Pesticide Science 51, 131-152). Examples include alcohol alkoxylates, such as coconut fat ethoxylate (10) or isotridecyl ethoxylate (12), fatty acid esters, for example, methyl esters of rapeseed oil or soy oil, amine alkoxylates fatty, for example, tallowamine ethoxylate (15), or ammonium and / or phosphonium salts, such as, for example, ammonium sulfate or diamonium hydrogen phosphate.

[00130] De preferncia, as formulaes compreendem entre 0,00000001% e 98% em peso de composto ativo ou, de um modo particularmente preferido, entre 0,01% e 95% em peso de composto ativo e, mais preferencialmente, entre 0,5% e 90% em peso de composto ativo, com base no peso da formulao. O teor em composto ativo definido com a soma do pelo menos um agente de controle biolgico e o pelo menos um fungicida (I).[00130] Preferably, the formulations comprise between 0.00000001% and 98% by weight of active compound or, particularly preferably, between 0.01% and 95% by weight of active compound and, more preferably, between 0 , 5% and 90% by weight of active compound, based on the weight of the formulation. The active compound content is defined as the sum of at least one biological control agent and at least one fungicide (I).

[00131] O teor em composto ativo nas formas de aplicao (produtos para a proteo de culturas), preparadas a partir das formulaes, pode variar em limites alargados. [00150] Caso o pelo menos um agente de controle biolgico e o pelo menos um fungicida (I), e, facultativamente, o pelo menos um fungicida (II), sejam empregues ou utilizados de um modo sequencial, ento prefervel tratar as plantas ou as partes de plantas (que inclui as sementes e as plantas que emergem a partir das sementes), os frutos colhidos e os vegetais de acordo com o mtodo seguinte: em primeiro lugar, aplicar o pelo menos um fungicida (I) e, facultativamente, o pelo menos um fungicida (II) s plantas ou s partes de plantas e, em segundo lugar, aplicar o agente de controle biolgico s mesmas plantas ou partes de plantas. O perodo de tempo entre a primeira e a segunda aplicaes num ciclo de crescimento (cultura) pode variar e depende do efeito que se pretenda alcanar. Por exemplo, a primeira aplicao efetuada para prevenir uma infestao da planta ou das partes da planta com insetos, caros, nematodes e/ou fitopatognicos (em particular, tal o caso do tratamento de sementes) ou para combater a infestao com insetos, caros, nematodes e/ou fitopatognicos (em particular, tal o caso do tratamento de plantas e de partes de plantas) e a segunda aplicao efetuada para prevenir ou para controlar a infestao com insetos, caros, nematodes e/ou fitopatognicos. Neste contexto, o controle significa que o agente de controle biolgico no capaz de exterminar completamente as pragas ou fungos fitopatognicos, mas capaz de manter a infestao num nvel aceitvel.[00150] If at least one biological control agent and at least one fungicide (I), and, optionally, at least one fungicide (II), are employed or used sequentially, then it is preferable to treat the plants or the parts of plants (including the seeds and plants that emerge from the seeds), the harvested fruits and vegetables according to the following method: first, apply at least one fungicide (I) and, optionally , the at least one fungicide (II) to plants or parts of plants and, secondly, apply the biological control agent to the same plants or parts of plants. The length of time between the first and second applications in a growth cycle (culture) can vary and depends on the effect you want to achieve. For example, the first application is carried out to prevent infestation of the plant or parts of the plant with insects, mites, nematodes and / or phytopathogens (in particular, this is the case for seed treatment) or to combat infestation with insects, mites, nematodes and / or phytopathogens (in particular, this is the case for the treatment of plants and parts of plants) and the second application is carried out to prevent or to control infestation with insects, mites, nematodes and / or phytopathogens. In this context, control means that the biological control agent is not able to completely exterminate phytopathogenic pests or fungi, but is able to keep the infestation at an acceptable level.

[00178] Para o propsito da presente inveno, a composio de acordo com a inveno aplicada semente por si s ou numa formulao adequada. De preferncia, a semente tratada num estado suficientemente estvel de modo que o tratamento no cause qualquer dano. De um modo geral, a semente pode ser tratada em qualquer momento deste a colheita at ao semeio. De um modo habitual, a semente utilizada separada da planta e liberta de espigas, cascas, caules, pelos ou carne dos frutos. Assim, por exemplo, possvel utilizar sementes que tenham sido colhidas, limpas e secas at um teor em humidade inferior a 15% em peso. Em alternativa, tambm possvel utilizar sementes que, aps secagem, tenham sido tratadas, por exemplo, com gua e depois novamente secas.[00178] For the purpose of the present invention, the composition according to the invention is applied to the seed alone or in a suitable formulation. Preferably, the seed is treated in a sufficiently stable state so that the treatment does not cause any harm. In general, the seed can be treated at any time from harvest to sowing. In a usual way, the seed used is separated from the plant and freed from ears, barks, stems, hair or meat from the fruits. Thus, for example, it is possible to use seeds that have been harvested, cleaned and dried to a moisture content of less than 15% by weight. Alternatively, it is also possible to use seeds that, after drying, have been treated, for example, with water and then dried again.

[00179] Durante o tratamento das sementes, dever ser normalmente garantido que a quantidade da composio de acordo com a inveno e/ou a quantidade de outros aditivos aplicada s sementes, seja selecionada de um modo tal que a germinao da semente no seja prejudicada ou que a planta resultante no seja danificada. Tal dever ser particularmente garantido no caso de compostos ativos que possam exibir efeitos fitotxicos para determinadas taxas de aplicao.[00179] During seed treatment, it should normally be ensured that the amount of the composition according to the invention and / or the amount of other additives applied to the seeds, is selected in such a way that the germination of the seed is not impaired or that the resulting plant is not damaged. This should be particularly guaranteed in the case of active compounds that may exhibit phytotoxic effects at certain rates of application.

[00223] Os fungicidas podem ser utilizados na proteo de culturas para o controle de fungos fitopatognicos. Estes so caracterizados por uma eficcia extraordinria contra um espectro alargado de fungos fitopatognicos, incluindo patgenos provenientes do solo, os quais so, em particular, membros das classes Plasmodiophoromycetes, Peronosporomycetes (Syn. Oomycetes), Chytridiomycetes,[00223] Fungicides can be used in crop protection to control phytopathogenic fungi. These are characterized by their extraordinary effectiveness against a wide spectrum of phytopathogenic fungi, including pathogens from the soil, which are, in particular, members of the classes Plasmodiophoromycetes, Peronosporomycetes (Syn. Oomycetes), Chytridiomycetes,

Zygomycetes, Ascomycetes, Basidiomycetes e Deuteromycetes (Syn. Fungi imperfecti). Alguns fungicidas so ativos sob o ponto de vista sistmico e podem ser utilizados na proteo de plantas como revestimentos foliares, revestimento para sementes ou fungicidas para o solo. Some fungicides are active from a systemic point of view and can be used to protect plants such as leaf coatings, seed coatings or soil fungicides. In addition, they are suitable for combating fungi, which infest, for example, wood and plant roots.

[00246] As composies da inveno podem ser utilizadas para um controle curativo ou protetivo/preventivo de fungos fitopatognicos. Assim sendo, a inveno tambm diz respeito a mtodos curativos e protetivos para o controle de fungos fitopatognicos por meio da utilizao dos ingredientes ativos ou composies da inveno, os quais so aplicados s sementes, s plantas ou a partes da planta, ao fruto ou ao solo no qual as plantas crescem.[00246] The compositions of the invention can be used for a curative or protective / preventive control of phytopathogenic fungi. Therefore, the invention also concerns curative and protective methods for the control of phytopathogenic fungi through the use of the active ingredients or compositions of the invention, which are applied to the seeds, plants or parts of the plant, the fruit or the soil on which plants grow.

[00247] O fato de a composio ser bem tolerada pelas plantas nas concentraes necessrias para o controle de doenas de plantas permite o tratamento de partes areas de plantas, de enxertos e sementes de propagao e do solo.[00247] The fact that the composition is well tolerated by plants in the concentrations necessary for the control of plant diseases allows the treatment of aerial parts of plants, grafts and propagating seeds and soil.

[00248] De acordo com a inveno possvel tratar todas as plantas e partes de plantas. Por plantas pretende-se designar todas as plantas e populaes de plantas, tais como plantas selvagens, cultivares e variedades de plantas, desejveis ou indesejveis (estejam ou no protegidas por direitos de variedades de plantas ou direitos de criadores de plantas). Typically, such plants are prepared by crossing a sterile inbred male parent line (female parent) with another inbred male fertile parent line (male parent). Typically, hybrid seeds are harvested from sterile male plants and sold to producers. Sterile male plants can sometimes (e.g., in maize) be produced by

Petio 870190055580, de 17/06/2019, pg. 94/130Petition 870190055580, of 06/17/2019, p. 94/130

89/110 corte da pancula, isto , remoo mecnica dos rgos reprodutores masculinos (ou flores macho), embora, mais tipicamente, a esterilidade masculina seja resultado de determinantes genticos no genoma da planta. Neste caso, e particularmente quando a semente constitui o produto desejado que se pretende colher a partir das plantas hbridas, tipicamente til garantir que a fertilidade masculina nas plantas hbridas, seja totalmente restaurada. Tal pode ser efetuado garantindo que as progenitoras masculinas possuem os genes restauradores de fertilidade adequados, os quais so capazes de restaurar a fertilidade masculina nas plantas hbridas que contm os determinantes genticos responsveis pela esterilidade masculina. Os determinantes genticos para a esterilidade masculina podem estar localizados no citoplasma. Exemplos de esterilidade masculina citoplsmica (CMS) foram descritos, por exemplo, para a espcie Brassica. No entanto, os determinantes genticos para a esterilidade masculina tambm podem estar localizados no genoma nuclear. As plantas com esterilidade masculina tambm podem ser obtidas por mtodos biotecnolgicos de plantas, tais como engenharia gentica. Um meio particularmente til para se obter plantas com esterilidade masculina encontra-se descrito no documento WO 89/10396, no qual, por exemplo, uma ribonuclease, tal como barnase, seletivamente expressa em clulas tapetum nos estames. A fertilidade pode ento ser restaurada por expresso nas clulas tapetum de um inibidor de ribonuclease, tal como barstar.89/110 cut of the panicle, that is, mechanical removal of the male reproductive organs (or male flowers), although, more typically, male sterility is the result of genetic determinants in the plant's genome. In this case, and particularly when the seed is the desired product to be harvested from hybrid plants, it is typically useful to ensure that male fertility in hybrid plants is fully restored. This can be done by ensuring that male parents have the appropriate fertility restoring genes, which are capable of restoring male fertility in hybrid plants that contain the genetic determinants responsible for male sterility. The genetic determinants for male sterility may be located in the cytoplasm. Examples of cytoplasmic male sterility (CMS) have been described, for example, for the species Brassica. However, the genetic determinants for male sterility can also be located in the nuclear genome. Plants with male sterility can also be obtained by plant biotechnological methods, such as genetic engineering. A particularly useful means of obtaining plants with male sterility is described in WO 89/10396, in which, for example, a ribonuclease, such as barnase, is selectively expressed in tapetum cells in the stamens. Fertility can then be restored by expression in the tapetum cells of a ribonuclease inhibitor, such as barstar.

Por exemplo, plantas tolerantes a glifosato podem ser obtidas por meio da transformao da planta com um gene que codifica a enzima 5-enolpiruvilshiquimato-3fosfato sintase (EPSPS). Como exemplos de tais genes EPSPS referese o gene AroA (mutante CT7) da bactria Salmonella typhimurium, o gene CP4 da bactria Agrobacterium sp., os genes que codificam uma EPSPS de petnia, uma EPSPS de tomate ou uma EPSPS de eleusina. Tambm podem ser uma EPSPS mutada. As plantas tolerantes a glifosato tambm podem ser obtidas por meio da expresso de um gene que codifica uma enzima glifosato oxidoredutase. As plantas tolerantes a glifosato tambm podem ser obtidas por meio da expresso de um gene que codifica uma enzima glifosato acetil-transferase. As plantas tolerantes a glifosato tambm podem ser obtidas por meio da seleo de plantas que contm mutaes que ocorrem naturalmente dos genes supramencionados.90/110 [00260] Herbicide tolerant plants are, for example, glyphosate tolerant plants, that is, plants made tolerant to the herbicide glyphosate or its salts. Plants can be made tolerant to glyphosate by different means. For example, glyphosate-tolerant plants can be obtained by transforming the plant with a gene that encodes the enzyme 5-enolpyruvylshiquimate-3 phosphate synthase (EPSPS). Examples of such EPSPS genes include the AroA gene (CT7 mutant) of the bacterium Salmonella typhimurium, the CP4 gene of the bacterium Agrobacterium sp., The genes encoding a petunia EPSPS, a tomato EPSPS or an eleusin EPSPS. They can also be a mutated EPSPS. Glyphosate-tolerant plants can also be obtained by expressing a gene that encodes a glyphosate oxidoreductase enzyme. Glyphosate-tolerant plants can also be obtained by expressing a gene that encodes a glyphosate acetyl transferase enzyme. Glyphosate-tolerant plants can also be obtained by selecting plants that contain naturally occurring mutations of the aforementioned genes.

[00261] Como outras plantas resistentes a herbicidas refere-se, por exemplo, plantas que so tornadas tolerantes a herbicidas que inibem a enzima glutamina sintase, tais como bialafos, fosfinotricina ou glufosinato. Tais plantas podem ser obtidas por meio de expresso de uma enzima desintoxicante do herbicida ou uma enzima glutamina sintase mutante que seja resistente a inibio. Uma tal enzima desintoxicante eficaz uma enzima que codifica uma fosfinotricina acetil-transferase (tal como, por exemplo, a protena bar ou pat proveniente da espcie Streptomyces). Plantas que expressam uma fosfinotricina acetil-transferase exgena foram j descritas.[00261] Like other herbicide-resistant plants there are, for example, plants that are made tolerant to herbicides that inhibit the enzyme glutamine synthase, such as bialafos, phosphinothricin or glufosinate. Such plants can be obtained by expressing a detoxifying enzyme from the herbicide or a mutant glutamine synthase enzyme that is resistant to inhibition. Such an effective detoxifying enzyme is an enzyme encoding a phosphinothricin acetyl transferase (such as, for example, the bar or pat protein from the species Streptomyces). Plants that express an exogenous phosphinothricin acetyl transferase have already been described.

[00262] Alm disso, outras plantas tolerantes a herbicidas so tambm plantas que so tornadas tolerantes a herbicidas que inibem a[00262] In addition, other herbicide-tolerant plants are also plants that are made tolerant to herbicides that inhibit

Petio 870190055580, de 17/06/2019, pg. 96/130Petition 870190055580, of 06/17/2019, p. 96/130

91/110 enzima hidroxifenilpiruvato-dioxigenase (HPPD). As hidroxifenilpiruvato-dioxigenases so enzimas que catalisam a reao pela qual para-hidroxifenilpiruvato (HPP) transformado em homogentisato. As plantas tolerantes a inibidores de HPPD podem ser transformadas com um gene que codifica uma enzima HPPD resistente que ocorra naturalmente ou um gene que codifica uma enzima HPPD mutada. A tolerncia a inibidores de HPPD tambm pode ser obtida por meio da transformao de plantas com genes que codificam determinadas enzimas que permitem a formao de homogentisato apesar da inibio da enzima HPPD nativa pelo inibidor de HPPD. Hydroxyphenylpyruvate-dioxigenases are enzymes that catalyze the reaction by which parahydroxyphenylpyruvate (HPP) is transformed into homogentisate. Plants tolerant to HPPD inhibitors can be transformed with a gene encoding a naturally occurring resistant HPPD enzyme or a gene encoding a mutated HPPD enzyme. Tolerance to HPPD inhibitors can also be obtained by transforming plants with genes that encode certain enzymes that allow the formation of homogentisate despite the inhibition of the native HPPD enzyme by the HPPD inhibitor. Plant tolerance to HPPD inhibitors can also be improved by transforming plants with a gene that encodes a prefenate dehydrogenase enzyme in addition to a gene that encodes an HPPD-tolerant enzyme.

[00263] Outras plantas resistentes a herbicidas so plantas que so tornadas tolerantes a inibidores de acetolactato sintase (ALS). Como inibidores de ALS conhecidos refere-se, por exemplo, os herbicidas sulfonilureia, imidazolinona, triazolopirimidinas, pirimidiniloxi(tio)benzoatos e/ou sulfonilaminocarbonil-triazolinona. So conhecidas diferentes mutaes na enzima ALS (tambm conhecida como acetohidroxi-cido sintase, AHAS) que conferem tolerncia a herbicidas e grupos de herbicidas diferentes. A produo de plantas tolerantes a sulfonilureia e de plantas tolerantes a imidazolinona encontra-se descrita no documento WO 1996/033270. Outras plantas tolerantes a imidazolinona tambm se encontram descritas. Outras plantas tolerantes a sulfonilureia e imidazolinona tambm se encontram descritas, por exemplo, no documento WO 2007/024782.[00263] Other herbicide-resistant plants are plants that are made tolerant to acetolactate synthase (ALS) inhibitors. Known ALS inhibitors include, for example, the herbicides sulfonylurea, imidazolinone, triazolopyrimidines, pyrimidinyloxy (thio) benzoates and / or sulfonylaminocarbonyl-triazolinone. Different mutations in the ALS enzyme (also known as acetohydroxy acid synthase, AHAS) are known to confer tolerance to different herbicides and groups of herbicides. The production of sulfonylurea tolerant plants and imidazolinone tolerant plants is described in WO 1996/033270. Other imidazolinone tolerant plants are also described. Other plants tolerant to sulfonylurea and imidazolinone are also described, for example, in WO 2007/024782.

[00274] Como plantas transgnicas particularmente teis que possvel tratar de acordo com a inveno refere-se plantas que contm eventos de transformao, ou uma combinao de eventos de transformao, e que se encontram listadas, por exemplo, em bases de dados de diversas agncias reguladoras nacionais ou regionais (ver, por exemplo, http://gmoinfo.jrc.it/gmp_browse.aspx e http://www.agbios.com/dbase.php).[00274] As particularly useful transgenic plants that can be treated according to the invention are plants that contain transformation events, or a combination of transformation events, and which are listed, for example, in databases of different national or regional regulatory agencies (see, for example, http://gmoinfo.jrc.it/gmp_browse.aspx and http://www.agbios.com/dbase.php).

Exemplos [00275] A atividade fungicida avanada das combinaes de compostos ativos de acordo com a inveno evidente a partir do exemplo seguinte. Ao passo que os compostos ativos individuais exibem resultados fracos no que diz respeito atividade fungicida, as combinaes possuem uma atividade que excede a adio simples de atividades.Examples [00275] The advanced fungicidal activity of the combinations of active compounds according to the invention is evident from the following example. While the individual active compounds show poor results with respect to fungicidal activity, the combinations have an activity that exceeds the simple addition of activities.

[00276] Um efeito sinrgico de fungicidas est sempre presente quando a atividade fungicida das combinaes de compostos ativos excede o total das atividades dos compostos ativos, quando estes so aplicados individualmente. a atividade esperada para uma determinada combinao de dois compostos ativos pode ser calculada do seguinte modo (de acordo com a Frmula de Colby) (ver, Colby,[00276] A synergistic effect of fungicides is always present when the fungicidal activity of the combinations of active compounds exceeds the total activities of the active compounds, when they are applied individually. the expected activity for a given combination of two active compounds can be calculated as follows (according to Colby's Formula) (see, Colby,

Combinations, Weeds 1967, 15, 20-22):Combinations, Weeds 1967, 15, 20-22):

se o smbolo X representa a eficcia quando o composto ativo A aplicado a uma taxa de aplicao de m p.p.m. (ou g/ha), o smbolo Y representa a eficcia quando o composto ativo B aplicado a uma taxa de aplicao de n p.p.m. (ou g/ha), o smbolo E representa a eficcia quando os compostos ativos A e B so aplicados a taxas de aplicao de m e n p.p.m. (ou g/ha), respectivamente,whether X represents effectiveness when active compound A is applied at an application rate of m p.p.m. (or g / ha), the symbol Y represents the effectiveness when the active compound B is applied at an application rate of n p.p.m. (or g / ha), the symbol E represents the effectiveness when the active compounds A and B are applied at rates of application of m and n p.p.m. (or g / ha), respectively,

ento So E = X + Y - X-Y 100E = X + Y - X - Y 100

[00277] O grau de eficcia, expresso em percentagem (%), apresentado. Um valor de 0% designa uma eficcia que corresponde do controle, ao passo que uma eficcia de 100% designa que no observada doena.[00277] The degree of effectiveness, expressed as a percentage (%), is presented. A value of 0% designates an efficacy that corresponds to that of the control, whereas a 100% efficacy designates that no disease is observed.

[00278] Caso a atividade fungicida real exceda o valor calculado, ento a atividade da combinao sobreaditiva, isto , est presente um efeito sinrgico. Neste caso, a eficcia realmente observada dever ser superior ao valor esperado de eficcia (E), calculado a partir da frmula supramencionada.[00278] If the actual fungicidal activity exceeds the calculated value, then the activity of the combination is over-additive, that is, a synergistic effect is present. In this case, the effectiveness actually observed should be higher than the expected value of effectiveness (E), calculated from the formula mentioned above.

[00279] Uma outra forma de demonstrar um efeito sinrgico o mtodo de Tammes (ver, Isoboles, a graphic representation of synergism in pesticides em Neth. J. Plant Path., 1964, 70, 73-80).[00279] Another way to demonstrate a synergistic effect is the Tammes method (see, "Isoboles, the graphic representation of synergism in pesticides" in Neth. J. Plant Path., 1964, 70, 73-80).

Foi utilizada uma soluo que compreende 8,5 x 108 CFU/g (1,34%) desta cepa.[00281] In the following examples, the strain of Bacillus subtilis AQ30002 was used, which is referred to before as B19 and is referred to in the following table as QST3002. A solution comprising 8.5 x 10 8 CFU / g (1.34%) of this strain was used.

Teste de Venturia (mas) / preventivo [00282] Diluiu-se QST30002 (B19), compostos ativos (1 parte em peso) dissolvidos em acetona/dimetilacetamida (24,5/24,5 partes em peso) e ter alquilaril-poligliclico (1 parte em peso), ou suas combinaes, com gua at concentrao desejada.Venturia test (apples) / preventive [00282] QST30002 (B19), active compounds (1 part by weight) dissolved in acetone / dimethylacetamide (24.5 / 24.5 parts by weight) and alkylaryl-polyglycolic ether ( 1 part by weight), or their combinations, with water to the desired concentration.
